On August 3, 2022, the President signed three bills into law. The first one, H.R. 1057, is called the "Greatest Generation Commemorative Coin Act" and requires the minting of coins to commemorate the National World War II Memorial in Washington, D.C. The second bill, H.R. 1842, is called the "Harriet Tubman Bicentennial Commemorative Coin Act" and requires the minting of coins to recognize the bicentennial of Harriet Tubman's birth. Lastly, H.R. 3359, known as the "Homicide Victims' Families' Rights Act of 2021," establishes a framework for immediate family members of murder victims to request a review of case files in federal cold case murders. The President thanked the representatives and senators who led on these issues.